description:
A California-based company is actively seeking a Computer Vision Engineer to join our team. You will work on innovative projects involving cutting-edge machine learning and computer vision technologies.

Responsibilities:
Developing and optimizing computer vision algorithms (image recognition, segmentation, classification, object detection, and tracking);
Participating in the full product development lifecycle, from research and prototyping to deployment;
Maintaining and improving existing solutions;
Collaborating with engineers and analysts to implement projects.

Requirements:
At least 2 years of experience in Computer Vision;
Strong proficiency in Python and key libraries (OpenCV, NumPy, TensorFlow/PyTorch, scikit-image, etc.);
Experience developing and applying neural networks for computer vision tasks;
Familiarity with version control tools (Git);
Understanding of machine learning algorithms and principles;
Experience with data handling and preprocessing;
Basic proficiency in English (technical documentation).

Working Conditions:
Competitive salary based on candidate experience.
Opportunity to work on innovative projects utilizing advanced technologies;
Professional growth and career advancement opportunities;
Flexible schedule and remote work possibilities;
Friendly team and comfortable working environment.
English B1+.

*Для заключения контракта нужно иметь ИП.

